  "subtitle": null,
  "body": [
    {
      "text": "LIMITATIONS & FUTURE WORK",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "What it cannot do, and what is next.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "LIMITATIONS",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Track tensioner - one side.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "The tracks were printed on two different machines (Dreamer + Ender). Dimensional drift between them left one loop slightly looser, so a printed tensioner was added on that side.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Single-motor differential\u00a0 - practical side",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Both tracks share one input. There is no active steering - the differential responds to load, not command.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "PLA fatigue at the link pin holes.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "148 holes flexing every revolution. PLA is not fatigue-friendly; holes elongate over time.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Welded rivet heads.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Soldering-iron welds hold well at rest but can shear under repeated bending stress.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Dual-stepper drive.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "One motor per track.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "TPU for tracks and rivets.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Better fatigue life, quieter operation, and rivets that bend instead of shear.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Single-machine track print.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Reprint all 148 links on one printer. Removes the dimensional drift that required the tensioner.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Closed-loop feedback.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Add an IMU and wheel encoders. Move from open-loop step counting to actual heading control.",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "ETAD 130  \u00b7  B. MIRONOV",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Limitations & Future",
      "level": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "12 / 13",
      "level": 0
    }
  ],
